Margarornis is the genus of treerunners, birds in the family Furnariidae. Established by Ludwig Reichenbach in 1853, it contains the following species:
Ruddy treerunner, Margarornis rubiginosus
Star-chested treerunner, Margarornis stellatus
Beautiful treerunner, Margarornis bellulus
Pearled treerunner, Margarornis squamigerThe genus name Margarornis is composed of two Greek words:margaron, meaning "pearl" and ornis, meaning "bird".